elements.2211.03101_fcd330a2286022e3bf5813d9fc160: There is an increasing interest in Quantum Machine Learning (QML) models, how they work and for which applications they could be useful
elements.2211.03101_fd79aaa217a397ed0fd899549066c: There have been many different proposals on how classical data can be encoded and what circuit ans
elements.2211.03101_a3dd6cc0212264e88d86209de9a15: tze and measurement operators should be used to process the encoded data and measure the output state of an ansatz
elements.2211.03101_1848a658cd5dc4ab51ee7d83b9061: The choice of the aforementioned operators plays a determinant role in the expressive power of the QML model
elements.2211.03101_95b6e2bdae1544c14ec9060b63ab9: In this work we investigate how certain changes in the circuit structure change this expressivity
elements.2211.03101_cc74d19d6e2bc6ba0b8f4b089b775: We introduce both numerical and analytical tools to explore the effect that these operators have in the overall performance of the QML model
elements.2211.03101_c7e6b0972dfb11116ae8ebee575e1: These tools are based on previous work on the teacher-student scheme, the partial Fourier series and the averaged operator size
elements.2211.03101_fe646cf9641c0c6f13da7a6d315dd: We focus our analysis on simple QML models with two and three qubits and observe that increasing the number of parameterized and entangling gates leads to a more expressive model for certain circuit structures
elements.2211.03101_b479ac18b146b761cd4a30a5bf5ee: Also, on which qubit the measurement is performed affects the type of functions that QML models could learn
elements.2211.03101_f9f08c2f0a8c94513c27cc19d38e7: This work sketches the determinant role that the processing and measurement operators have on the expressive power of simple quantum circuits.
elements.2211.03101_4b53da092f54ea9142780c8f7fe91: In recent years, there is increasing interest in the capabilities of Quantum Machine Learning (QML) models and their potential applications
elements.2211.03101_9390e9777c458a1b5a77f4d0256f4: To better understand for what tasks a QML model could be potentially used for
elements.2211.03101_35ab1b31bc1397bf0ab3cb9ca20d1: , we first need to understand where its strengths and weaknesses
elements.2211.03101_5e84277fef1c68babc0ac4ee131a1: \cite{goal_of_QML, Alejandro_new, Maria_kernel, Sim_2019, paper_storage, TS_scheme, data_re-uploading, Lewenstein_2021, Sim_2019, new1, NEW2}
elements.2211.03101_a309444c9f8d9921572c277e4d330: A first step to better understand what a QML model is capable of, is to study its expressivity
elements.2211.03101_ff6d69a41c4f2ec577158a658aeae: It has been shown that a specific quantum circuit architecture can be used as a universal function approximator
elements.2211.03101_105acc64ee8ea2d9bb20a521e10c7: , i.e. it can approximate any classification function up to arbitrary precision
elements.2211.03101_33da351d2be347fec55f3b58fb6d2: further sheds light on how the encoding of the data fundamentally limits the expressivity of quantum models
elements.2211.03101_b01fce44f333e77e37027fb6294a5: It also verifies that parameterized QML models with arbitrary single rotations and entangling gates give rise to complex trigonometric functions
elements.2211.03101_53b5c2bfb5fedcbed4a92c775b408: Instead of focusing on the data encoding, other works study the importance of the trainable part of the quantum circuits (consisting of data independent but parameterized gates) to which we refer to as the processing part of the circuit
elements.2211.03101_e6d988aaa1db140c8c8f3bfc071a3: , the authors perform a structure optimization that aims to find a more hardware efficient architecture for the desired problem
elements.2211.03101_836c349bf86bc21e31cfbef62f32e: Finally, recent works focus on benchmarking different circuit structures both numerically
elements.2211.03101_77c7710e08d668ce6f5789566110b: How to choose an ansatz for a supervised QML task is still an open question
elements.2211.03101_e341db85fab0cbda3cd93e54d1465: tze that are used to find ground states in quantum chemistry
elements.2211.03101_a7fa1b50358f9691a9bf2e1e83055: or many-body physics are often inspired by the problem itself
elements.2211.03101_238d7141fdd8c5f573233c40e073b: and some understanding of the optimization problem at hand can help to find a well-suited ansatz
elements.2211.03101_b39d9f66e196a02216cf1739fa169: For QML applications this does not apply in general
elements.2211.03101_87026d57d880d31fb6ac58cf0654e: which might partially be because we still do not fully understand how specific parts of the processing and measurement operators affect the performance of the QML model
elements.2211.03101_a944a59f17ce391310e0e542f5fa6: Moreover, even for small quantum circuits with a few number of qubits, there are still some open questions: "How many parameterized gates should be used?", "How many entangling gates and where?", "Where should the circuit be measured?" and "Do ancilla qubits help improve the expressivity of the circuit?"
elements.2211.03101_61f84522cad55a8e67107409de899: Inspired by these questions, we aim to study the effect of the processing part of QML architectures
elements.2211.03101_21c4d0e0dbc1c63f1e2c5b797b9fd: We believe that the structure of the processing and measurement operators play a determinant role in the QML model performance
elements.2211.03101_b26d739a7fe34d4128c5b9e92ba12: Here the term performance characterizes the model's ability to learn through training
elements.2211.03101_a235a379ec0da4db8cd0eca379c9c: , the type of functions that it can express
elements.2211.03101_aa7383eff4d5b167c4c25cb305c5e: , i.e. extracting information from the input state to the readout qubit
elements.2211.03101_d3b88d4c6f5414dc494241fc24d10: We use both analytical and numerical tools to explore how the processing unitaries and measurement affect the properties of a QML model
elements.2211.03101_370833528750f4c86ec9c4a226231: We focus our analysis on simple quantum models with just 2-3 qubits, which help us better understand how different parts of the processing and measurement operators affect the performance
elements.2211.03101_6cd7182e29a4b46a18b827effbb55: This analysis allows us to understand how the processing architecture affects the expressivity of the whole model, at least for circuits with small amounts of qubits, with the hope to draw insights on how specific parts will affect the performance of more complicated architectures with more qubits
elements.2211.03101_b2b92bcfd0d594817a6b73983358e: We observe that increasing the number of parameterized and entangling gates leads to a more expressive model for certain circuit structures and that ancillary qubits help increasing the expressive power of the model
